S_H. NAME
Holberton Simple Shell
A a simple UNIX command-line interpreter
B Simple_shell

S_H.  SYNOPSIS
Simple_shell [command_string]

S_H. DESCRIPTION
Shell is a UNIX term for the interactive user interface with an operating system that reads and executes commands from standard input.

COMMANDS

help: shows help information for the shell
exit: quits the shell with a status code of STATUS (default is 0)
unsetenv [VALUE]: unsets the environment variable VALUE
setenv [VALUE]: sets the environment variable VALUE
env: prints the environment variables
cd [DIRECTORY]: changes the working directory
strchr: string chaaracter in a function.

Examples
#env
To set an environment variable
#help
shows help information for the shell


S_H. Return Value
Always 0 for success, other number means failure.

S_H. OVERVIEW
The shell reads commands from the terminal and executes them.


S_H. OPTIONS
Command options will be typed after the main command followed by a space
